OL,7,FThe case was brought by the parents of
OL,8,Fa Belfast primary school girl who were
OL,9,Fnot religious and who did not want
OL,10,Ftheir daughter to be raised as a
OL,11,FChristian.
OL,13,FThe controversy began when the child
OL,14,Fbegan to say prayers before meals at
OL,15,Fhome, telling her family she had
OL,16,Flearned to do so in school.
OL,18,FHer father objected and subsequently
OL,19,Ftook legal action.
